38#define MAX_TIME ((time_t)((1U << 31) - 1))
39
40void
41_kdc_fix_time(time_t **t)
42{
43 if(*t == NULL){
44 ALLOC(*t);
45 **t = MAX_TIME;
46 }
47 if(**t == 0) **t = MAX_TIME; /* fix for old clients */
48}

50static int
51realloc_method_data(METHOD_DATA *md)
52{
53 PA_DATA *pa;
54 pa = realloc(md->val, (md->len + 1) * sizeof(*md->val));
55 if(pa == NULL)
56 return ENOMEM;
57 md->val = pa;
58 md->len++;
59 return 0;
60}
61
62static void
63set_salt_padata(METHOD_DATA *md, Salt *salt)
64{
65 if (salt) {
66 realloc_method_data(md);
67 md->val[md->len - 1].padata_type = salt->type;
68 der_copy_octet_string(&salt->salt,
69 &md->val[md->len - 1].padata_value);
70 }
71}

73const PA_DATA*
74_kdc_find_padata(const KDC_REQ *req, int *start, int type)
75{
76 if (req->padata == NULL)
77 return NULL;
78
79 while((size_t)*start < req->padata->len){
80 (*start)++;
81 if(req->padata->val[*start - 1].padata_type == (unsigned)type)
82 return &req->padata->val[*start - 1];
83 }
84 return NULL;
85}

87/*
88 * This is a hack to allow predefined weak services, like afs to
89 * still use weak types
90 */
91
92krb5_boolean
93_kdc_is_weak_exception(krb5_principal principal, krb5_enctype etype)
94{
95 if (principal->name.name_string.len > 0 &&
96 strcmp(principal->name.name_string.val[0], "afs") == 0 &&
97 (etype == (krb5_enctype)ETYPE_DES_CBC_CRC
98 || etype == (krb5_enctype)ETYPE_DES_CBC_MD4
99 || etype == (krb5_enctype)ETYPE_DES_CBC_MD5))
100 return TRUE;
101 return FALSE;
102}

105/*
106 * Detect if `key' is the using the the precomputed `default_salt'.
107 */
108
109static krb5_boolean
110is_default_salt_p(const krb5_salt *default_salt, const Key *key)
111{
112 if (key->salt == NULL)
113 return TRUE;
114 if (default_salt->salttype != key->salt->type)
115 return FALSE;
116 if (krb5_data_cmp(&default_salt->saltvalue, &key->salt->salt))
117 return FALSE;
118 return TRUE;
119}
120
121/*
122 * return the first appropriate key of `princ' in `ret_key'. Look for
123 * all the etypes in (`etypes', `len'), stopping as soon as we find
124 * one, but preferring one that has default salt.
125 */
126
127krb5_error_code
128_kdc_find_etype(krb5_context context, krb5_boolean use_strongest_session_key,
129 krb5_boolean is_preauth, hdb_entry_ex *princ,
130 krb5_enctype *etypes, unsigned len,
131 krb5_enctype *ret_enctype, Key **ret_key)
132{
133 krb5_error_code ret;
134 krb5_salt def_salt;
135 krb5_enctype enctype = (krb5_enctype)ETYPE_NULL;
136 const krb5_enctype *p;
137 Key *key = NULL;
138 int i, k;
139
140 /* We'll want to avoid keys with v4 salted keys in the pre-auth case... */
141 ret = krb5_get_pw_salt(context, princ->entry.principal, &def_salt);
142 if (ret)
143 return ret;
144
145 ret = KRB5KDC_ERR_ETYPE_NOSUPP;
146
147 if (use_strongest_session_key) {
148
149 /*
150 * Pick the strongest key that the KDC, target service, and
151 * client all support, using the local cryptosystem enctype
152 * list in strongest-to-weakest order to drive the search.
153 *
154 * This is not what RFC4120 says to do, but it encourages
155 * adoption of stronger enctypes. This doesn't play well with
156 * clients that have multiple Kerberos client implementations
157 * available with different supported enctype lists.
158 */
159
160 /* drive the search with local supported enctypes list */
161 p = krb5_kerberos_enctypes(context);
162 for (i = 0;
163 p[i] != (krb5_enctype)ETYPE_NULL && enctype == (krb5_enctype)ETYPE_NULL;
164 i++) {
165 if (krb5_enctype_valid(context, p[i]) != 0 &&
166 !_kdc_is_weak_exception(princ->entry.principal, p[i]))
167 continue;
168
169 /* check that the client supports it too */
170 for (k = 0; k < len && enctype == (krb5_enctype)ETYPE_NULL; k++) {
171
172 if (p[i] != etypes[k])
173 continue;
174
175 /* check target princ support */
176 key = NULL;
177 while (hdb_next_enctype2key(context, &princ->entry, NULL,
178 p[i], &key) == 0) {
179 if (key->key.keyvalue.length == 0) {
180 ret = KRB5KDC_ERR_NULL_KEY;
181 continue;
182 }
183 enctype = p[i];
184 ret = 0;
185 if (is_preauth && ret_key != NULL &&
186 !is_default_salt_p(&def_salt, key))
187 continue;
188 }
189 }
190 }
191 } else {
192 /*
193 * Pick the first key from the client's enctype list that is
194 * supported by the cryptosystem and by the given principal.
195 *
196 * RFC4120 says we SHOULD pick the first _strong_ key from the
197 * client's list... not the first key... If the admin disallows
198 * weak enctypes in krb5.conf and selects this key selection
199 * algorithm, then we get exactly what RFC4120 says.
200 */
201 for(i = 0; ret != 0 && i < len; i++) {
202
203 if (krb5_enctype_valid(context, etypes[i]) != 0 &&
204 !_kdc_is_weak_exception(princ->entry.principal, etypes[i]))
205 continue;
206
207 key = NULL;
208 while (ret != 0 &&
209 hdb_next_enctype2key(context, &princ->entry, NULL,
210 etypes[i], &key) == 0) {
211 if (key->key.keyvalue.length == 0) {
212 ret = KRB5KDC_ERR_NULL_KEY;
213 continue;
214 }
215 enctype = etypes[i];
216 ret = 0;
217 if (is_preauth && ret_key != NULL &&
218 !is_default_salt_p(&def_salt, key))
219 continue;
220 }
221 }
222 }
223
224 if (enctype == (krb5_enctype)ETYPE_NULL) {
225 /*
226 * if the service principal is one for which there is a known 1DES
227 * exception and no other enctype matches both the client request and
228 * the service key list, provide a DES-CBC-CRC key.
229 */
230 if (ret_key == NULL &&
231 _kdc_is_weak_exception(princ->entry.principal, ETYPE_DES_CBC_CRC)) {
232 ret = 0;
233 enctype = ETYPE_DES_CBC_CRC;
234 } else {
235 ret = KRB5KDC_ERR_ETYPE_NOSUPP;
236 }
237 }
238
239 if (ret == 0) {
240 if (ret_enctype != NULL)
241 *ret_enctype = enctype;
242 if (ret_key != NULL)
243 *ret_key = key;
244 }
245
246 krb5_free_salt (context, def_salt);
247 return ret;
248}

250krb5_error_code
251_kdc_make_anonymous_principalname (PrincipalName *pn)
252{
253 pn->name_type = KRB5_NT_PRINCIPAL;
254 pn->name_string.len = 1;
255 pn->name_string.val = malloc(sizeof(*pn->name_string.val));
256 if (pn->name_string.val == NULL)
257 return ENOMEM;
258 pn->name_string.val[0] = strdup("anonymous");
259 if (pn->name_string.val[0] == NULL) {
260 free(pn->name_string.val);
261 pn->name_string.val = NULL;
262 return ENOMEM;
263 }
264 return 0;
265}

285void
286_kdc_log_timestamp(krb5_context context,
287 krb5_kdc_configuration *config,
288 const char *type,
289 KerberosTime authtime, KerberosTime *starttime,
290 KerberosTime endtime, KerberosTime *renew_till)
291{
292 char authtime_str[100], starttime_str[100],
293 endtime_str[100], renewtime_str[100];
294
295 krb5_format_time(context, authtime,
296 authtime_str, sizeof(authtime_str), TRUE);
297 if (starttime)
298 krb5_format_time(context, *starttime,
299 starttime_str, sizeof(starttime_str), TRUE);
300 else
301 strlcpy(starttime_str, "unset", sizeof(starttime_str));
302 krb5_format_time(context, endtime,
303 endtime_str, sizeof(endtime_str), TRUE);
304 if (renew_till)
305 krb5_format_time(context, *renew_till,
306 renewtime_str, sizeof(renewtime_str), TRUE);
307 else
308 strlcpy(renewtime_str, "unset", sizeof(renewtime_str));
309
310 kdc_log(context, config, 5,
311 "%s authtime: %s starttime: %s endtime: %s renew till: %s",
312 type, authtime_str, starttime_str, endtime_str, renewtime_str);
313}

321static krb5_error_code
322pa_pkinit_validate(kdc_request_t r, const PA_DATA *pa)
323{
324 pk_client_params *pkp = NULL;
325 char *client_cert = NULL;
326 krb5_error_code ret;
327
328 ret = _kdc_pk_rd_padata(r->context, r->config, &r->req, pa, r->client, &pkp);
329 if (ret || pkp == NULL) {
330 ret = KRB5KRB_AP_ERR_BAD_INTEGRITY;
331 _kdc_r_log(r, 5, "Failed to decode PKINIT PA-DATA -- %s",
332 r->client_name);
333 goto out;
334 }
335
336 ret = _kdc_pk_check_client(r->context,
337 r->config,
338 r->clientdb,
339 r->client,
340 pkp,
341 &client_cert);
342 if (ret) {
343 _kdc_set_e_text(r, "PKINIT certificate not allowed to "
344 "impersonate principal");
345 goto out;
346 }
347
348 _kdc_r_log(r, 0, "PKINIT pre-authentication succeeded -- %s using %s",
349 r->client_name, client_cert);
350 free(client_cert);
351
352 ret = _kdc_pk_mk_pa_reply(r->context, r->config, pkp, r->client,
353 r->sessionetype, &r->req, &r->request,
354 &r->reply_key, &r->session_key, &r->outpadata);
355 if (ret) {
356 _kdc_set_e_text(r, "Failed to build PK-INIT reply");
357 goto out;
358 }
359#if 0
360 ret = _kdc_add_inital_verified_cas(r->context, r->config,
361 pkp, &r->et);
362#endif
363 out:
364 if (pkp)
365 _kdc_pk_free_client_param(r->context, pkp);
366
367 return ret;
368}

376static krb5_error_code
377make_pa_enc_challange(krb5_context context, METHOD_DATA *md,
378 krb5_crypto crypto)
379{
380 PA_ENC_TS_ENC p;
381 unsigned char *buf;
382 size_t buf_size;
383 size_t len;
384 EncryptedData encdata;
385 krb5_error_code ret;
386 int32_t usec;
387 int usec2;
388
389 krb5_us_timeofday (context, &p.patimestamp, &usec);
390 usec2 = usec;
391 p.pausec = &usec2;
392
393 ASN1_MALLOC_ENCODE(PA_ENC_TS_ENC, buf, buf_size, &p, &len, ret);
394 if (ret)
395 return ret;
396 if(buf_size != len)
397 krb5_abortx(context, "internal error in ASN.1 encoder");
398
399 ret = krb5_encrypt_EncryptedData(context,
400 crypto,
401 KRB5_KU_ENC_CHALLENGE_KDC,
402 buf,
403 len,
404 0,
405 &encdata);
406 free(buf);
407 if (ret)
408 return ret;
409
410 ASN1_MALLOC_ENCODE(EncryptedData, buf, buf_size, &encdata, &len, ret);
411 free_EncryptedData(&encdata);
412 if (ret)
413 return ret;
414 if(buf_size != len)
415 krb5_abortx(context, "internal error in ASN.1 encoder");
416
417 ret = krb5_padata_add(context, md, KRB5_PADATA_ENCRYPTED_CHALLENGE, buf, len);
418 if (ret)
419 free(buf);
420 return ret;
421}

423static krb5_error_code
424pa_enc_chal_validate(kdc_request_t r, const PA_DATA *pa)
425{
426 krb5_data pepper1, pepper2, ts_data;
427 KDC_REQ_BODY *b = &r->req.req_body;
428 int invalidPassword = 0;
429 EncryptedData enc_data;
430 krb5_enctype aenctype;
431 krb5_error_code ret;
432 struct Key *k;
433 size_t size;
434 int i;
435
436 heim_assert(r->armor_crypto != NULL, "ENC-CHAL called for non FAST");
437
438 if (_kdc_is_anon_request(b)) {
439 ret = KRB5KRB_AP_ERR_BAD_INTEGRITY;
440 kdc_log(r->context, r->config, 0, "ENC-CHALL doesn't support anon");
441 return ret;
442 }
443
444 ret = decode_EncryptedData(pa->padata_value.data,
445 pa->padata_value.length,
446 &enc_data,
447 &size);
448 if (ret) {
449 ret = KRB5KRB_AP_ERR_BAD_INTEGRITY;
450 _kdc_r_log(r, 5, "Failed to decode PA-DATA -- %s",
451 r->client_name);
452 return ret;
453 }
454
455 pepper1.data = "clientchallengearmor";
456 pepper1.length = strlen(pepper1.data);
457 pepper2.data = "challengelongterm";
458 pepper2.length = strlen(pepper2.data);
459
460 krb5_crypto_getenctype(r->context, r->armor_crypto, &aenctype);
461
462 for (i = 0; i < r->client->entry.keys.len; i++) {
463 krb5_crypto challangecrypto, longtermcrypto;
464 krb5_keyblock challangekey;
465 PA_ENC_TS_ENC p;
466
467 k = &r->client->entry.keys.val[i];
468
469 ret = krb5_crypto_init(r->context, &k->key, 0, &longtermcrypto);
470 if (ret)
471 continue;
472
473 ret = krb5_crypto_fx_cf2(r->context, r->armor_crypto, longtermcrypto,
474 &pepper1, &pepper2, aenctype,
475 &challangekey);
476 krb5_crypto_destroy(r->context, longtermcrypto);
477 if (ret)
478 continue;
479
480 ret = krb5_crypto_init(r->context, &challangekey, 0,
481 &challangecrypto);
482 if (ret)
483 continue;
484
485 ret = krb5_decrypt_EncryptedData(r->context, challangecrypto,
486 KRB5_KU_ENC_CHALLENGE_CLIENT,
487 &enc_data,
488 &ts_data);
489 if (ret) {
490 const char *msg = krb5_get_error_message(r->context, ret);
491 krb5_error_code ret2;
492 char *str = NULL;
493
494 invalidPassword = 1;
495
496 ret2 = krb5_enctype_to_string(r->context, k->key.keytype, &str);
497 if (ret2)
498 str = NULL;
499 _kdc_r_log(r, 5, "Failed to decrypt ENC-CHAL -- %s "
500 "(enctype %s) error %s",
501 r->client_name, str ? str : "unknown enctype", msg);
502 krb5_free_error_message(r->context, msg);
503 free(str);
504
505 continue;
506 }
507
508 ret = decode_PA_ENC_TS_ENC(ts_data.data,
509 ts_data.length,
510 &p,
511 &size);
512 krb5_data_free(&ts_data);
513 if(ret){
514 krb5_crypto_destroy(r->context, challangecrypto);
515 ret = KRB5KDC_ERR_PREAUTH_FAILED;
516 _kdc_r_log(r, 5, "Failed to decode PA-ENC-TS_ENC -- %s",
517 r->client_name);
518 continue;
519 }
520
521 if (labs(kdc_time - p.patimestamp) > r->context->max_skew) {
522 char client_time[100];
523
524 krb5_crypto_destroy(r->context, challangecrypto);
525
526 krb5_format_time(r->context, p.patimestamp,
527 client_time, sizeof(client_time), TRUE);
528
529 ret = KRB5KRB_AP_ERR_SKEW;
530 _kdc_r_log(r, 0, "Too large time skew, "
531 "client time %s is out by %u > %u seconds -- %s",
532 client_time,
533 (unsigned)labs(kdc_time - p.patimestamp),
534 r->context->max_skew,
535 r->client_name);
536
537 free_PA_ENC_TS_ENC(&p);
538 goto out;
539 }
540
541 free_PA_ENC_TS_ENC(&p);
542
543 ret = make_pa_enc_challange(r->context, &r->outpadata,
544 challangecrypto);
545 krb5_crypto_destroy(r->context, challangecrypto);
546 if (ret)
547 goto out;
548
549 set_salt_padata(&r->outpadata, k->salt);
550 krb5_free_keyblock_contents(r->context, &r->reply_key);
551 ret = krb5_copy_keyblock_contents(r->context, &k->key, &r->reply_key);
552 if (ret)
553 goto out;
554
555 /*
556 * Success
557 */
558 if (r->clientdb->hdb_auth_status)
559 r->clientdb->hdb_auth_status(r->context, r->clientdb, r->client,
560 HDB_AUTH_SUCCESS);
561 goto out;
562 }
563
564 if (invalidPassword && r->clientdb->hdb_auth_status) {
565 r->clientdb->hdb_auth_status(r->context, r->clientdb, r->client,
566 HDB_AUTH_WRONG_PASSWORD);
567 ret = KRB5KDC_ERR_PREAUTH_FAILED;
568 }
569 out:
570 free_EncryptedData(&enc_data);
571
572 return ret;
573}

575static krb5_error_code
576pa_enc_ts_validate(kdc_request_t r, const PA_DATA *pa)
577{
578 EncryptedData enc_data;
579 krb5_error_code ret;
580 krb5_crypto crypto;
581 krb5_data ts_data;
582 PA_ENC_TS_ENC p;
583 size_t len;
584 Key *pa_key;
585 char *str;
586
587 if (_kdc_is_anon_request(&r->req.req_body)) {
588 ret = KRB5KRB_AP_ERR_BAD_INTEGRITY;
589 _kdc_set_e_text(r, "ENC-TS doesn't support anon");
590 goto out;
591 }
592
593 ret = decode_EncryptedData(pa->padata_value.data,
594 pa->padata_value.length,
595 &enc_data,
596 &len);
597 if (ret) {
598 ret = KRB5KRB_AP_ERR_BAD_INTEGRITY;
599 _kdc_r_log(r, 5, "Failed to decode PA-DATA -- %s",
600 r->client_name);
601 goto out;
602 }
603
604 ret = hdb_enctype2key(r->context, &r->client->entry, NULL,
605 enc_data.etype, &pa_key);
606 if(ret){
607 char *estr;
608 _kdc_set_e_text(r, "No key matching entype");
609 ret = KRB5KDC_ERR_ETYPE_NOSUPP;
610 if(krb5_enctype_to_string(r->context, enc_data.etype, &estr))
611 estr = NULL;
612 if(estr == NULL)
613 _kdc_r_log(r, 5,
614 "No client key matching pa-data (%d) -- %s",
615 enc_data.etype, r->client_name);
616 else
617 _kdc_r_log(r, 5,
618 "No client key matching pa-data (%s) -- %s",
619 estr, r->client_name);
620 free(estr);
621 free_EncryptedData(&enc_data);
622 goto out;
623 }
624
625 try_next_key:
626 ret = krb5_crypto_init(r->context, &pa_key->key, 0, &crypto);
627 if (ret) {
628 const char *msg = krb5_get_error_message(r->context, ret);
629 _kdc_r_log(r, 0, "krb5_crypto_init failed: %s", msg);
630 krb5_free_error_message(r->context, msg);
631 free_EncryptedData(&enc_data);
632 goto out;
633 }
634
635 ret = krb5_decrypt_EncryptedData (r->context,
636 crypto,
637 KRB5_KU_PA_ENC_TIMESTAMP,
638 &enc_data,
639 &ts_data);
640 krb5_crypto_destroy(r->context, crypto);
641 /*
642 * Since the user might have several keys with the same
643 * enctype but with diffrent salting, we need to try all
644 * the keys with the same enctype.
645 */
646 if(ret){
647 krb5_error_code ret2;
648 const char *msg = krb5_get_error_message(r->context, ret);
649
650 ret2 = krb5_enctype_to_string(r->context,
651 pa_key->key.keytype, &str);
652 if (ret2)
653 str = NULL;
654 _kdc_r_log(r, 5, "Failed to decrypt PA-DATA -- %s "
655 "(enctype %s) error %s",
656 r->client_name, str ? str : "unknown enctype", msg);
657 krb5_free_error_message(r->context, msg);
658 free(str);
659
660 if(hdb_next_enctype2key(r->context, &r->client->entry, NULL,
661 enc_data.etype, &pa_key) == 0)
662 goto try_next_key;
663
664 free_EncryptedData(&enc_data);
665
666 if (r->clientdb->hdb_auth_status)
667 r->clientdb->hdb_auth_status(r->context, r->clientdb, r->client,
668 HDB_AUTH_WRONG_PASSWORD);
669
670 ret = KRB5KDC_ERR_PREAUTH_FAILED;
671 goto out;
672 }
673 free_EncryptedData(&enc_data);
674 ret = decode_PA_ENC_TS_ENC(ts_data.data,
675 ts_data.length,
676 &p,
677 &len);
678 krb5_data_free(&ts_data);
679 if(ret){
680 ret = KRB5KDC_ERR_PREAUTH_FAILED;
681 _kdc_r_log(r, 5, "Failed to decode PA-ENC-TS_ENC -- %s",
682 r->client_name);
683 goto out;
684 }
685 if (labs(kdc_time - p.patimestamp) > r->context->max_skew) {
686 char client_time[100];
687
688 krb5_format_time(r->context, p.patimestamp,
689 client_time, sizeof(client_time), TRUE);
690
691 ret = KRB5KRB_AP_ERR_SKEW;
692 _kdc_r_log(r, 0, "Too large time skew, "
693 "client time %s is out by %u > %u seconds -- %s",
694 client_time,
695 (unsigned)labs(kdc_time - p.patimestamp),
696 r->context->max_skew,
697 r->client_name);
698
699 /*
700 * The following is needed to make windows clients to
701 * retry using the timestamp in the error message, if
702 * there is a e_text, they become unhappy.
703 */
704 r->e_text = NULL;
705 free_PA_ENC_TS_ENC(&p);
706 goto out;
707 }
708 free_PA_ENC_TS_ENC(&p);
709
710 set_salt_padata(&r->outpadata, pa_key->salt);
711
712 ret = krb5_copy_keyblock_contents(r->context, &pa_key->key, &r->reply_key);
713 if (ret)
714 return ret;
715
716 ret = krb5_enctype_to_string(r->context, pa_key->key.keytype, &str);
717 if (ret)
718 str = NULL;
719 _kdc_r_log(r, 2, "ENC-TS Pre-authentication succeeded -- %s using %s",
720 r->client_name, str ? str : "unknown enctype");
721 free(str);
722
723 ret = 0;
724
725 out:
726
727 return ret;
728}

775static void
776log_patypes(krb5_context context,
777 krb5_kdc_configuration *config,
778 METHOD_DATA *padata)
779{
780 struct rk_strpool *p = NULL;
781 char *str;
782 size_t n, m;
783
784 for (n = 0; n < padata->len; n++) {
785 for (m = 0; m < sizeof(pat) / sizeof(pat[0]); m++) {
786 if (padata->val[n].padata_type == pat[m].type) {
787 p = rk_strpoolprintf(p, "%s", pat[m].name);
788 break;
789 }
790 }
791 if (m == sizeof(pat) / sizeof(pat[0]))
792 p = rk_strpoolprintf(p, "%d", padata->val[n].padata_type);
793 if (p && n + 1 < padata->len)
794 p = rk_strpoolprintf(p, ", ");
795 if (p == NULL) {
796 kdc_log(context, config, 0, "out of memory");
797 return;
798 }
799 }
800 if (p == NULL)
801 p = rk_strpoolprintf(p, "none");
802
803 str = rk_strpoolcollect(p);
804 kdc_log(context, config, 0, "Client sent patypes: %s", str);
805 free(str);
806}

808/*
809 *
810 */
811
812krb5_error_code
813_kdc_encode_reply(krb5_context context,
814 krb5_kdc_configuration *config,
815 krb5_crypto armor_crypto, uint32_t nonce,
816 KDC_REP *rep, EncTicketPart *et, EncKDCRepPart *ek,
817 krb5_enctype etype,
818 int skvno, const EncryptionKey *skey,
819 int ckvno, const EncryptionKey *reply_key,
820 int rk_is_subkey,
821 const char **e_text,
822 krb5_data *reply)
823{
824 unsigned char *buf;
825 size_t buf_size;
826 size_t len = 0;
827 krb5_error_code ret;
828 krb5_crypto crypto;
829
830 ASN1_MALLOC_ENCODE(EncTicketPart, buf, buf_size, et, &len, ret);
831 if(ret) {
832 const char *msg = krb5_get_error_message(context, ret);
833 kdc_log(context, config, 0, "Failed to encode ticket: %s", msg);
834 krb5_free_error_message(context, msg);
835 return ret;
836 }
837 if(buf_size != len)
838 krb5_abortx(context, "Internal error in ASN.1 encoder");
839
840 ret = krb5_crypto_init(context, skey, etype, &crypto);
841 if (ret) {
842 const char *msg = krb5_get_error_message(context, ret);
843 kdc_log(context, config, 0, "krb5_crypto_init failed: %s", msg);
844 krb5_free_error_message(context, msg);
845 free(buf);
846 return ret;
847 }
848
849 ret = krb5_encrypt_EncryptedData(context,
850 crypto,
851 KRB5_KU_TICKET,
852 buf,
853 len,
854 skvno,
855 &rep->ticket.enc_part);
856 free(buf);
857 krb5_crypto_destroy(context, crypto);
858 if(ret) {
859 const char *msg = krb5_get_error_message(context, ret);
860 kdc_log(context, config, 0, "Failed to encrypt data: %s", msg);
861 krb5_free_error_message(context, msg);
862 return ret;
863 }
864
865 if (armor_crypto) {
866 krb5_data data;
867 krb5_keyblock *strengthen_key = NULL;
868 KrbFastFinished finished;
869
870 kdc_log(context, config, 0, "FAST armor protection");
871
872 memset(&finished, 0, sizeof(finished));
873 krb5_data_zero(&data);
874
875 finished.timestamp = kdc_time;
876 finished.usec = 0;
877 finished.crealm = et->crealm;
878 finished.cname = et->cname;
879
880 ASN1_MALLOC_ENCODE(Ticket, data.data, data.length,
881 &rep->ticket, &len, ret);
882 if (ret)
883 return ret;
884 if (data.length != len)
885 krb5_abortx(context, "internal asn.1 error");
886
887 ret = krb5_create_checksum(context, armor_crypto,
888 KRB5_KU_FAST_FINISHED, 0,
889 data.data, data.length,
890 &finished.ticket_checksum);
891 krb5_data_free(&data);
892 if (ret)
893 return ret;
894
895 ret = _kdc_fast_mk_response(context, armor_crypto,
896 rep->padata, strengthen_key, &finished,
897 nonce, &data);
898 free_Checksum(&finished.ticket_checksum);
899 if (ret)
900 return ret;
901
902 if (rep->padata) {
903 free_METHOD_DATA(rep->padata);
904 } else {
905 rep->padata = calloc(1, sizeof(*(rep->padata)));
906 if (rep->padata == NULL) {
907 krb5_data_free(&data);
908 return ENOMEM;
909 }
910 }
911
912 ret = krb5_padata_add(context, rep->padata,
913 KRB5_PADATA_FX_FAST,
914 data.data, data.length);
915 if (ret)
916 return ret;
917
918 /*
919 * Hide client name of privacy reasons
920 */
921 if (1 /* r->fast_options.hide_client_names */) {
922 rep->crealm[0] = '\0';
923 free_PrincipalName(&rep->cname);
924 rep->cname.name_type = 0;
925 }
926 }
927
928 if(rep->msg_type == krb_as_rep && !config->encode_as_rep_as_tgs_rep)
929 ASN1_MALLOC_ENCODE(EncASRepPart, buf, buf_size, ek, &len, ret);
930 else
931 ASN1_MALLOC_ENCODE(EncTGSRepPart, buf, buf_size, ek, &len, ret);
932 if(ret) {
933 const char *msg = krb5_get_error_message(context, ret);
934 kdc_log(context, config, 0, "Failed to encode KDC-REP: %s", msg);
935 krb5_free_error_message(context, msg);
936 return ret;
937 }
938 if(buf_size != len) {
939 free(buf);
940 kdc_log(context, config, 0, "Internal error in ASN.1 encoder");
941 *e_text = "KDC internal error";
942 return KRB5KRB_ERR_GENERIC;
943 }
944 ret = krb5_crypto_init(context, reply_key, 0, &crypto);
945 if (ret) {
946 const char *msg = krb5_get_error_message(context, ret);
947 free(buf);
948 kdc_log(context, config, 0, "krb5_crypto_init failed: %s", msg);
949 krb5_free_error_message(context, msg);
950 return ret;
951 }
952 if(rep->msg_type == krb_as_rep) {
953 krb5_encrypt_EncryptedData(context,
954 crypto,
955 KRB5_KU_AS_REP_ENC_PART,
956 buf,
957 len,
958 ckvno,
959 &rep->enc_part);
960 free(buf);
961 ASN1_MALLOC_ENCODE(AS_REP, buf, buf_size, rep, &len, ret);
962 } else {
963 krb5_encrypt_EncryptedData(context,
964 crypto,
965 rk_is_subkey ? KRB5_KU_TGS_REP_ENC_PART_SUB_KEY : KRB5_KU_TGS_REP_ENC_PART_SESSION,
966 buf,
967 len,
968 ckvno,
969 &rep->enc_part);
970 free(buf);
971 ASN1_MALLOC_ENCODE(TGS_REP, buf, buf_size, rep, &len, ret);
972 }
973 krb5_crypto_destroy(context, crypto);
974 if(ret) {
975 const char *msg = krb5_get_error_message(context, ret);
976 kdc_log(context, config, 0, "Failed to encode KDC-REP: %s", msg);
977 krb5_free_error_message(context, msg);
978 return ret;
979 }
980 if(buf_size != len) {
981 free(buf);
982 kdc_log(context, config, 0, "Internal error in ASN.1 encoder");
983 *e_text = "KDC internal error";
984 return KRB5KRB_ERR_GENERIC;
985 }
986 reply->data = buf;
987 reply->length = buf_size;
988 return 0;
989}

991/*

993 * determining if the server should send ETYPE_INFO2 or not.

996static int
997older_enctype(krb5_enctype enctype)
998{
999 switch (enctype) {
1000 case ETYPE_DES_CBC_CRC:
1001 case ETYPE_DES_CBC_MD4:
1002 case ETYPE_DES_CBC_MD5:
1003 case ETYPE_DES3_CBC_SHA1:
1004 case ETYPE_ARCFOUR_HMAC_MD5:
1005 case ETYPE_ARCFOUR_HMAC_MD5_56:
1006 /*

1008 * windows 2000 hosts.
1009 */
1010 case ETYPE_ARCFOUR_MD4:
1011 case ETYPE_ARCFOUR_HMAC_OLD:
1012 case ETYPE_ARCFOUR_HMAC_OLD_EXP:
1013 return 1;
1014 default:
1015 return 0;
1016 }
1017}

1112extern int _krb5_AES_SHA1_string_to_default_iterator;
1113extern int _krb5_AES_SHA2_string_to_default_iterator;
1114
1115static krb5_error_code
1116make_s2kparams(int value, size_t len, krb5_data **ps2kparams)
1117{
1118 krb5_data *s2kparams;
1119 krb5_error_code ret;
1120
1121 ALLOC(s2kparams);
1122 if (s2kparams == NULL)
1123 return ENOMEM;
1124 ret = krb5_data_alloc(s2kparams, len);
1125 if (ret) {
1126 free(s2kparams);
1127 return ret;
1128 }
1129 _krb5_put_int(s2kparams->data, value, len);
1130 *ps2kparams = s2kparams;
1131 return 0;
1132}
1133
1134static krb5_error_code
1135make_etype_info2_entry(ETYPE_INFO2_ENTRY *ent, Key *key)
1136{
1137 krb5_error_code ret;
1138
1139 ent->etype = key->key.keytype;
1140 if(key->salt) {
1141 ALLOC(ent->salt);
1142 if (ent->salt == NULL)
1143 return ENOMEM;
1144 *ent->salt = malloc(key->salt->salt.length + 1);
1145 if (*ent->salt == NULL) {
1146 free(ent->salt);
1147 ent->salt = NULL;
1148 return ENOMEM;
1149 }
1150 memcpy(*ent->salt, key->salt->salt.data, key->salt->salt.length);
1151 (*ent->salt)[key->salt->salt.length] = '\0';
1152 } else
1153 ent->salt = NULL;
1154
1155 ent->s2kparams = NULL;
1156
1157 switch (key->key.keytype) {
1158 case ETYPE_AES128_CTS_HMAC_SHA1_96:
1159 case ETYPE_AES256_CTS_HMAC_SHA1_96:
1160 ret = make_s2kparams(_krb5_AES_SHA1_string_to_default_iterator,
1161 4, &ent->s2kparams);
1162 break;
1163 case KRB5_ENCTYPE_AES128_CTS_HMAC_SHA256_128:
1164 case KRB5_ENCTYPE_AES256_CTS_HMAC_SHA384_192:
1165 ret = make_s2kparams(_krb5_AES_SHA2_string_to_default_iterator,
1166 4, &ent->s2kparams);
1167 break;
1168 case ETYPE_DES_CBC_CRC:
1169 case ETYPE_DES_CBC_MD4:
1170 case ETYPE_DES_CBC_MD5:
1171 /* Check if this was a AFS3 salted key */
1172 if(key->salt && key->salt->type == hdb_afs3_salt)
1173 ret = make_s2kparams(1, 1, &ent->s2kparams);
1174 else
1175 ret = 0;
1176 break;
1177 default:
1178 ret = 0;
1179 break;
1180 }
1181 return ret;
1182}

1292/*
1293 * verify the flags on `client' and `server', returning 0
1294 * if they are OK and generating an error messages and returning
1295 * and error code otherwise.
1296 */
1297
1298krb5_error_code
1299kdc_check_flags(krb5_context context,
1300 krb5_kdc_configuration *config,
1301 hdb_entry_ex *client_ex, const char *client_name,
1302 hdb_entry_ex *server_ex, const char *server_name,
1303 krb5_boolean is_as_req)
1304{
1305 if(client_ex != NULL) {
1306 hdb_entry *client = &client_ex->entry;
1307
1308 /* check client */
1309 if (client->flags.locked_out) {
1310 kdc_log(context, config, 0,
1311 "Client (%s) is locked out", client_name);
1312 return KRB5KDC_ERR_POLICY;
1313 }
1314
1315 if (client->flags.invalid) {
1316 kdc_log(context, config, 0,
1317 "Client (%s) has invalid bit set", client_name);
1318 return KRB5KDC_ERR_POLICY;
1319 }
1320
1321 if(!client->flags.client){
1322 kdc_log(context, config, 0,
1323 "Principal may not act as client -- %s", client_name);
1324 return KRB5KDC_ERR_POLICY;
1325 }
1326
1327 if (client->valid_start && *client->valid_start > kdc_time) {
1328 char starttime_str[100];
1329 krb5_format_time(context, *client->valid_start,
1330 starttime_str, sizeof(starttime_str), TRUE);
1331 kdc_log(context, config, 0,
1332 "Client not yet valid until %s -- %s",
1333 starttime_str, client_name);
1334 return KRB5KDC_ERR_CLIENT_NOTYET;
1335 }
1336
1337 if (client->valid_end && *client->valid_end < kdc_time) {
1338 char endtime_str[100];
1339 krb5_format_time(context, *client->valid_end,
1340 endtime_str, sizeof(endtime_str), TRUE);
1341 kdc_log(context, config, 0,
1342 "Client expired at %s -- %s",
1343 endtime_str, client_name);
1344 return KRB5KDC_ERR_NAME_EXP;
1345 }
1346
1347 if (client->flags.require_pwchange &&
1348 (server_ex == NULL || !server_ex->entry.flags.change_pw)) {
1349 kdc_log(context, config, 0,
1350 "Client's key must be changed -- %s", client_name);
1351 return KRB5KDC_ERR_KEY_EXPIRED;
1352 }
1353
1354 if (client->pw_end && *client->pw_end < kdc_time
1355 && (server_ex == NULL || !server_ex->entry.flags.change_pw)) {
1356 char pwend_str[100];
1357 krb5_format_time(context, *client->pw_end,
1358 pwend_str, sizeof(pwend_str), TRUE);
1359 kdc_log(context, config, 0,
1360 "Client's key has expired at %s -- %s",
1361 pwend_str, client_name);
1362 return KRB5KDC_ERR_KEY_EXPIRED;
1363 }
1364 }
1365
1366 /* check server */
1367
1368 if (server_ex != NULL) {
1369 hdb_entry *server = &server_ex->entry;
1370
1371 if (server->flags.locked_out) {
1372 kdc_log(context, config, 0,
1373 "Client server locked out -- %s", server_name);
1374 return KRB5KDC_ERR_POLICY;
1375 }
1376 if (server->flags.invalid) {
1377 kdc_log(context, config, 0,
1378 "Server has invalid flag set -- %s", server_name);
1379 return KRB5KDC_ERR_POLICY;
1380 }
1381
1382 if(!server->flags.server){
1383 kdc_log(context, config, 0,
1384 "Principal may not act as server -- %s", server_name);
1385 return KRB5KDC_ERR_POLICY;
1386 }
1387
1388 if(!is_as_req && server->flags.initial) {
1389 kdc_log(context, config, 0,
1390 "AS-REQ is required for server -- %s", server_name);
1391 return KRB5KDC_ERR_POLICY;
1392 }
1393
1394 if (server->valid_start && *server->valid_start > kdc_time) {
1395 char starttime_str[100];
1396 krb5_format_time(context, *server->valid_start,
1397 starttime_str, sizeof(starttime_str), TRUE);
1398 kdc_log(context, config, 0,
1399 "Server not yet valid until %s -- %s",
1400 starttime_str, server_name);
1401 return KRB5KDC_ERR_SERVICE_NOTYET;
1402 }
1403
1404 if (server->valid_end && *server->valid_end < kdc_time) {
1405 char endtime_str[100];
1406 krb5_format_time(context, *server->valid_end,
1407 endtime_str, sizeof(endtime_str), TRUE);
1408 kdc_log(context, config, 0,
1409 "Server expired at %s -- %s",
1410 endtime_str, server_name);
1411 return KRB5KDC_ERR_SERVICE_EXP;
1412 }
1413
1414 if (server->pw_end && *server->pw_end < kdc_time) {
1415 char pwend_str[100];
1416 krb5_format_time(context, *server->pw_end,
1417 pwend_str, sizeof(pwend_str), TRUE);
1418 kdc_log(context, config, 0,
1419 "Server's key has expired at -- %s",
1420 pwend_str, server_name);
1421 return KRB5KDC_ERR_KEY_EXPIRED;
1422 }
1423 }
1424 return 0;
1425}

1427/*
1428 * Return TRUE if `from' is part of `addresses' taking into consideration
1429 * the configuration variables that tells us how strict we should be about
1430 * these checks
1431 */
1432
1433krb5_boolean
1434_kdc_check_addresses(krb5_context context,
1435 krb5_kdc_configuration *config,
1436 HostAddresses *addresses, const struct sockaddr *from)
1437{
1438 krb5_error_code ret;
1439 krb5_address addr;
1440 krb5_boolean result;
1441 krb5_boolean only_netbios = TRUE;
1442 size_t i;
1443
1444 if(config->check_ticket_addresses == 0)
1445 return TRUE;
1446
1447 if(addresses == NULL)
1448 return config->allow_null_ticket_addresses;
1449
1450 for (i = 0; i < addresses->len; ++i) {
1451 if (addresses->val[i].addr_type != KRB5_ADDRESS_NETBIOS) {
1452 only_netbios = FALSE;
1453 }
1454 }
1455
1456 /* Windows sends it's netbios name, which I can only assume is
1457 * used for the 'allowed workstations' check. This is painful,
1458 * but we still want to check IP addresses if they happen to be
1459 * present.
1460 */
1461
1462 if(only_netbios)
1463 return config->allow_null_ticket_addresses;
1464
1465 ret = krb5_sockaddr2address (context, from, &addr);
1466 if(ret)
1467 return FALSE;
1468
1469 result = krb5_address_search(context, &addr, addresses);
1470 krb5_free_address (context, &addr);
1471 return result;
1472}

1475 *
1476 */
1477
1478static krb5_boolean
1479send_pac_p(krb5_context context, KDC_REQ *req)
1480{
1481 krb5_error_code ret;
1482 PA_PAC_REQUEST pacreq;
1483 const PA_DATA *pa;
1484 int i = 0;
1485
1486 pa = _kdc_find_padata(req, &i, KRB5_PADATA_PA_PAC_REQUEST);
1487 if (pa == NULL)
1488 return TRUE;
1489
1490 ret = decode_PA_PAC_REQUEST(pa->padata_value.data,
1491 pa->padata_value.length,
1492 &pacreq,
1493 NULL);
1494 if (ret)
1495 return TRUE;
1496 i = pacreq.include_pac;
1497 free_PA_PAC_REQUEST(&pacreq);
1498 if (i == 0)
1499 return FALSE;
1500 return TRUE;
1501}

1503/*
1504 *
1505 */
1506
1507static krb5_error_code
1508generate_pac(kdc_request_t r, Key *skey)
1509{
1510 krb5_error_code ret;
1511 krb5_pac p = NULL;
1512 krb5_data data;
1513
1514 ret = _kdc_pac_generate(r->context, r->client, &p);
1515 if (ret) {
1516 _kdc_r_log(r, 0, "PAC generation failed for -- %s",
1517 r->client_name);
1518 return ret;
1519 }
1520 if (p == NULL)
1521 return 0;

1524 r->client->entry.principal,

1530 _kdc_r_log(r, 0, "PAC signing failed for -- %s",

1532 return ret;
1533 }
1534
1535 ret = _kdc_tkt_add_if_relevant_ad(r->context, &r->et,
1536 KRB5_AUTHDATA_WIN2K_PAC,
1537 &data);
1538 krb5_data_free(&data);
1539
1540 return ret;
1541}

1546
1547krb5_boolean
1548_kdc_is_anonymous(krb5_context context, krb5_principal principal)
1549{
1550 if ((principal->name.name_type != KRB5_NT_WELLKNOWN &&
1551 principal->name.name_type != KRB5_NT_UNKNOWN) ||
1552 principal->name.name_string.len != 2 ||
1553 strcmp(principal->name.name_string.val[0], KRB5_WELLKNOWN_NAME) != 0 ||
1554 strcmp(principal->name.name_string.val[1], KRB5_ANON_NAME) != 0)
1555 return 0;
1556 return 1;
1557}

1568/*
1569 *
1570 */
1571
1572static krb5_error_code
1573add_enc_pa_rep(kdc_request_t r)
1574{
1575 krb5_error_code ret;
1576 krb5_crypto crypto;
1577 Checksum checksum;
1578 krb5_data cdata;
1579 size_t len;
1580
1581 ret = krb5_crypto_init(r->context, &r->reply_key, 0, &crypto);
1582 if (ret)
1583 return ret;
1584
1585 ret = krb5_create_checksum(r->context, crypto,
1586 KRB5_KU_AS_REQ, 0,
1587 r->request.data, r->request.length,
1588 &checksum);
1589 krb5_crypto_destroy(r->context, crypto);
1590 if (ret)
1591 return ret;
1592
1593 ASN1_MALLOC_ENCODE(Checksum, cdata.data, cdata.length,
1594 &checksum, &len, ret);
1595 free_Checksum(&checksum);
1596 if (ret)
1597 return ret;
1598 heim_assert(cdata.length == len, "ASN.1 internal error");
1599
1600 if (r->ek.encrypted_pa_data == NULL) {
1601 ALLOC(r->ek.encrypted_pa_data);
1602 if (r->ek.encrypted_pa_data == NULL)
1603 return ENOMEM;
1604 }
1605 ret = krb5_padata_add(r->context, r->ek.encrypted_pa_data,
1606 KRB5_PADATA_REQ_ENC_PA_REP, cdata.data, cdata.length);
1607 if (ret)
1608 return ret;
1609
1610 return krb5_padata_add(r->context, r->ek.encrypted_pa_data,
1611 KRB5_PADATA_FX_FAST, NULL, 0);
1612}
1613
1614/*
1615 *
1616 */
1617
1618krb5_error_code
1619_kdc_as_rep(kdc_request_t r,
1620 krb5_data *reply,
1621 const char *from,
1622 struct sockaddr *from_addr,
1623 int datagram_reply)
1624{
1625 krb5_context context = r->context;
1626 krb5_kdc_configuration *config = r->config;
1627 KDC_REQ *req = &r->req;
1628 KDC_REQ_BODY *b = NULL;
1629 AS_REP rep;
1630 KDCOptions f;
1631 krb5_enctype setype;
1632 krb5_error_code ret = 0;
1633 Key *skey;
1634 int found_pa = 0;
1635 int i, flags = HDB_F_FOR_AS_REQ;
1636 METHOD_DATA error_method;
1637 const PA_DATA *pa;
1638
1639 memset(&rep, 0, sizeof(rep));
1640 error_method.len = 0;
1641 error_method.val = NULL;
1642
1643 /*
1644 * Look for FAST armor and unwrap
1645 */
1646 ret = _kdc_fast_unwrap_request(r);
1647 if (ret) {
1648 _kdc_r_log(r, 0, "FAST unwrap request from %s failed: %d", from, ret);
1649 goto out;
1650 }
1651
1652 b = &req->req_body;
1653 f = b->kdc_options;
1654
1655 if (f.canonicalize)
1656 flags |= HDB_F_CANON;
1657
1658 if(b->sname == NULL){
1659 ret = KRB5KRB_ERR_GENERIC;
1660 _kdc_set_e_text(r, "No server in request");
1661 } else{
1662 ret = _krb5_principalname2krb5_principal (context,
1663 &r->server_princ,
1664 *(b->sname),
1665 b->realm);
1666 if (ret == 0)
1667 ret = krb5_unparse_name(context, r->server_princ, &r->server_name);
1668 }
1669 if (ret) {
1670 kdc_log(context, config, 0,
1671 "AS-REQ malformed server name from %s", from);
1672 goto out;
1673 }
1674 if(b->cname == NULL){
1675 ret = KRB5KRB_ERR_GENERIC;
1676 _kdc_set_e_text(r, "No client in request");
1677 } else {
1678 ret = _krb5_principalname2krb5_principal (context,
1679 &r->client_princ,
1680 *(b->cname),
1681 b->realm);
1682 if (ret)
1683 goto out;
1684
1685 ret = krb5_unparse_name(context, r->client_princ, &r->client_name);
1686 }
1687 if (ret) {
1688 kdc_log(context, config, 0,
1689 "AS-REQ malformed client name from %s", from);
1690 goto out;
1691 }
1692
1693 kdc_log(context, config, 0, "AS-REQ %s from %s for %s",
1694 r->client_name, from, r->server_name);
1695
1696 /*
1697 *
1698 */
1699
1700 if (_kdc_is_anonymous(context, r->client_princ)) {
1701 if (!_kdc_is_anon_request(b)) {
1702 kdc_log(context, config, 0, "Anonymous ticket w/o anonymous flag");
1703 ret = KRB5KDC_ERR_C_PRINCIPAL_UNKNOWN;
1704 goto out;
1705 }
1706 } else if (_kdc_is_anon_request(b)) {
1707 kdc_log(context, config, 0,
1708 "Request for a anonymous ticket with non "
1709 "anonymous client name: %s", r->client_name);
1710 ret = KRB5KDC_ERR_C_PRINCIPAL_UNKNOWN;
1711 goto out;
1712 }
1713
1714 /*
1715 *
1716 */
1717
1718 ret = _kdc_db_fetch(context, config, r->client_princ,
1719 HDB_F_GET_CLIENT | flags, NULL,
1720 &r->clientdb, &r->client);
1721 if(ret == HDB_ERR_NOT_FOUND_HERE) {
1722 kdc_log(context, config, 5, "client %s does not have secrets at this KDC, need to proxy",
1723 r->client_name);
1724 goto out;
1725 } else if (ret == HDB_ERR_WRONG_REALM) {
1726 char *fixed_client_name = NULL;
1727
1728 ret = krb5_unparse_name(context, r->client->entry.principal,
1729 &fixed_client_name);
1730 if (ret) {
1731 goto out;
1732 }
1733
1734 kdc_log(context, config, 0, "WRONG_REALM - %s -> %s",
1735 r->client_name, fixed_client_name);
1736 free(fixed_client_name);
1737
1738 ret = _kdc_fast_mk_error(context, r,
1739 &error_method,
1740 r->armor_crypto,
1741 &req->req_body,
1742 KRB5_KDC_ERR_WRONG_REALM,
1743 NULL,
1744 r->server_princ,
1745 NULL,
1746 &r->client->entry.principal->realm,
1747 NULL, NULL,
1748 reply);
1749 goto out;
1750 } else if(ret){
1751 const char *msg = krb5_get_error_message(context, ret);
1752 kdc_log(context, config, 0, "UNKNOWN -- %s: %s", r->client_name, msg);
1753 krb5_free_error_message(context, msg);
1754 ret = KRB5KDC_ERR_C_PRINCIPAL_UNKNOWN;
1755 goto out;
1756 }
1757 ret = _kdc_db_fetch(context, config, r->server_princ,
1758 HDB_F_GET_SERVER|HDB_F_GET_KRBTGT | flags,
1759 NULL, NULL, &r->server);
1760 if(ret == HDB_ERR_NOT_FOUND_HERE) {
1761 kdc_log(context, config, 5, "target %s does not have secrets at this KDC, need to proxy",
1762 r->server_name);
1763 goto out;
1764 } else if(ret){
1765 const char *msg = krb5_get_error_message(context, ret);
1766 kdc_log(context, config, 0, "UNKNOWN -- %s: %s", r->server_name, msg);
1767 krb5_free_error_message(context, msg);
1768 ret = KRB5KDC_ERR_S_PRINCIPAL_UNKNOWN;
1769 goto out;
1770 }
1771
1772 /*
1773 * Select a session enctype from the list of the crypto system
1774 * supported enctypes that is supported by the client and is one of
1775 * the enctype of the enctype of the service (likely krbtgt).
1776 *
1777 * The latter is used as a hint of what enctypes all KDC support,
1778 * to make sure a newer version of KDC won't generate a session
1779 * enctype that an older version of a KDC in the same realm can't
1780 * decrypt.
1781 */
1782
1783 ret = _kdc_find_etype(context,
1784 krb5_principal_is_krbtgt(context, r->server_princ) ?
1785 config->tgt_use_strongest_session_key :
1786 config->svc_use_strongest_session_key, FALSE,
1787 r->client, b->etype.val, b->etype.len, &r->sessionetype,
1788 NULL);
1789 if (ret) {
1790 kdc_log(context, config, 0,
1791 "Client (%s) from %s has no common enctypes with KDC "
1792 "to use for the session key",
1793 r->client_name, from);
1794 goto out;
1795 }
1796
1797 /*
1798 * Pre-auth processing
1799 */
1800
1801 if(req->padata){
1802 unsigned int n;
1803
1804 log_patypes(context, config, req->padata);
1805
1806 /* Check if preauth matching */
1807
1808 for (n = 0; !found_pa && n < sizeof(pat) / sizeof(pat[0]); n++) {
1809 if (pat[n].validate == NULL)
1810 continue;
1811 if (r->armor_crypto == NULL && (pat[n].flags & PA_REQ_FAST))
1812 continue;
1813
1814 kdc_log(context, config, 5,
1815 "Looking for %s pa-data -- %s", pat[n].name, r->client_name);
1816 i = 0;
1817 pa = _kdc_find_padata(req, &i, pat[n].type);
1818 if (pa) {
1819 ret = pat[n].validate(r, pa);
1820 if (ret != 0) {
1821 goto out;
1822 }
1823 kdc_log(context, config, 0,
1824 "%s pre-authentication succeeded -- %s",
1825 pat[n].name, r->client_name);
1826 found_pa = 1;
1827 r->et.flags.pre_authent = 1;
1828 }
1829 }
1830 }
1831
1832 if (found_pa == 0) {
1833 Key *ckey = NULL;
1834 size_t n;
1835
1836 for (n = 0; n < sizeof(pat) / sizeof(pat[0]); n++) {
1837 if ((pat[n].flags & PA_ANNOUNCE) == 0)
1838 continue;
1839 ret = krb5_padata_add(context, &error_method,
1840 pat[n].type, NULL, 0);
1841 if (ret)
1842 goto out;
1843 }
1844
1845 /*
1846 * If there is a client key, send ETYPE_INFO{,2}
1847 */
1848 ret = _kdc_find_etype(context,
1849 config->preauth_use_strongest_session_key, TRUE,
1850 r->client, b->etype.val, b->etype.len, NULL, &ckey);
1851 if (ret == 0) {
1852
1853 /*
1854 * RFC4120 requires:
1855 * - If the client only knows about old enctypes, then send
1856 * both info replies (we send 'info' first in the list).
1857 * - If the client is 'modern', because it knows about 'new'
1858 * enctype types, then only send the 'info2' reply.
1859 *
1860 * Before we send the full list of etype-info data, we pick
1861 * the client key we would have used anyway below, just pick
1862 * that instead.
1863 */
1864
1865 if (older_enctype(ckey->key.keytype)) {
1866 ret = get_pa_etype_info(context, config,
1867 &error_method, ckey);
1868 if (ret)
1869 goto out;
1870 }
1871 ret = get_pa_etype_info2(context, config,
1872 &error_method, ckey);
1873 if (ret)
1874 goto out;
1875 }
1876
1877 /*
1878 * send requre preauth is its required or anon is requested,
1879 * anon is today only allowed via preauth mechanisms.
1880 */
1881 if (require_preauth_p(r) || _kdc_is_anon_request(b)) {
1882 ret = KRB5KDC_ERR_PREAUTH_REQUIRED;
1883 _kdc_set_e_text(r, "Need to use PA-ENC-TIMESTAMP/PA-PK-AS-REQ");
1884 goto out;
1885 }
1886
1887 if (ckey == NULL) {
1888 ret = KRB5KDC_ERR_CLIENT_NOTYET;
1889 _kdc_set_e_text(r, "Doesn't have a client key available");
1890 goto out;
1891 }
1892 krb5_free_keyblock_contents(r->context, &r->reply_key);
1893 ret = krb5_copy_keyblock_contents(r->context, &ckey->key, &r->reply_key);
1894 if (ret)
1895 goto out;
1896 }
1897
1898 if (r->clientdb->hdb_auth_status) {
1899 r->clientdb->hdb_auth_status(context, r->clientdb, r->client,
1900 HDB_AUTH_SUCCESS);
1901 }
1902
1903 /*
1904 * Verify flags after the user been required to prove its identity
1905 * with in a preauth mech.
1906 */
1907
1908 ret = _kdc_check_access(context, config, r->client, r->client_name,
1909 r->server, r->server_name,
1910 req, &error_method);
1911 if(ret)
1912 goto out;
1913
1914 /*
1915 * Select the best encryption type for the KDC with out regard to
1916 * the client since the client never needs to read that data.
1917 */
1918
1919 ret = _kdc_get_preferred_key(context, config,
1920 r->server, r->server_name,
1921 &setype, &skey);
1922 if(ret)
1923 goto out;
1924
1925 if(f.renew || f.validate || f.proxy || f.forwarded || f.enc_tkt_in_skey
1926 || (_kdc_is_anon_request(b) && !config->allow_anonymous)) {
1927 ret = KRB5KDC_ERR_BADOPTION;
1928 _kdc_set_e_text(r, "Bad KDC options");
1929 goto out;
1930 }
1931
1932 /*
1933 * Build reply
1934 */
1935
1936 rep.pvno = 5;
1937 rep.msg_type = krb_as_rep;
1938
1939 if (_kdc_is_anonymous(context, r->client_princ)) {
1940 Realm anon_realm=KRB5_ANON_REALM;
1941 ret = copy_Realm(&anon_realm, &rep.crealm);
1942 } else
1943 ret = copy_Realm(&r->client->entry.principal->realm, &rep.crealm);
1944 if (ret)
1945 goto out;
1946 ret = _krb5_principal2principalname(&rep.cname, r->client->entry.principal);
1947 if (ret)
1948 goto out;
1949
1950 rep.ticket.tkt_vno = 5;
1951 copy_Realm(&r->server->entry.principal->realm, &rep.ticket.realm);
1952 _krb5_principal2principalname(&rep.ticket.sname,
1953 r->server->entry.principal);
1954 /* java 1.6 expects the name to be the same type, lets allow that
1955 * uncomplicated name-types. */
1956#define CNT(sp,t) (((sp)->sname->name_type) == KRB5_NT_##t)
1957 if (CNT(b, UNKNOWN) || CNT(b, PRINCIPAL) || CNT(b, SRV_INST) || CNT(b, SRV_HST) || CNT(b, SRV_XHST))
1958 rep.ticket.sname.name_type = b->sname->name_type;
1959#undef CNT
1960
1961 r->et.flags.initial = 1;
1962 if(r->client->entry.flags.forwardable && r->server->entry.flags.forwardable)
1963 r->et.flags.forwardable = f.forwardable;
1964 else if (f.forwardable) {
1965 _kdc_set_e_text(r, "Ticket may not be forwardable");
1966 ret = KRB5KDC_ERR_POLICY;
1967 goto out;
1968 }
1969 if(r->client->entry.flags.proxiable && r->server->entry.flags.proxiable)
1970 r->et.flags.proxiable = f.proxiable;
1971 else if (f.proxiable) {
1972 _kdc_set_e_text(r, "Ticket may not be proxiable");
1973 ret = KRB5KDC_ERR_POLICY;
1974 goto out;
1975 }
1976 if(r->client->entry.flags.postdate && r->server->entry.flags.postdate)
1977 r->et.flags.may_postdate = f.allow_postdate;
1978 else if (f.allow_postdate){
1979 _kdc_set_e_text(r, "Ticket may not be postdate");
1980 ret = KRB5KDC_ERR_POLICY;
1981 goto out;
1982 }
1983
1984 /* check for valid set of addresses */
1985 if(!_kdc_check_addresses(context, config, b->addresses, from_addr)) {
1986 _kdc_set_e_text(r, "Bad address list in requested");
1987 ret = KRB5KRB_AP_ERR_BADADDR;
1988 goto out;
1989 }
1990
1991 ret = copy_PrincipalName(&rep.cname, &r->et.cname);
1992 if (ret)
1993 goto out;
1994 ret = copy_Realm(&rep.crealm, &r->et.crealm);
1995 if (ret)
1996 goto out;
1997
1998 {
1999 time_t start;
2000 time_t t;
2001
2002 start = r->et.authtime = kdc_time;
2003
2004 if(f.postdated && req->req_body.from){
2005 ALLOC(r->et.starttime);
2006 start = *r->et.starttime = *req->req_body.from;
2007 r->et.flags.invalid = 1;
2008 r->et.flags.postdated = 1; /* XXX ??? */
2009 }
2010 _kdc_fix_time(&b->till);
2011 t = *b->till;
2012
2013 /* be careful not overflowing */
2014
